sequenceDiagram
    participant R as Requester
    participant M as Manager
    participant FD as Finance Director
    participant P as Procurement
    participant V as Vendor
    participant F as Finance

    R->>M: Submit purchase request
    M-->>R: PR approved
    Note over M,FD: SOX Control: Spend threshold check ($50,000)
    alt Amount > $50,000
        M->>FD: Route for second approval (SOX segregation of duties)
        FD->>FD: Review spend justification
        FD-->>M: Second approval granted
        M->>P: Forward approved PR (dual approval)
    else Amount ≤ $50,000
        M->>P: Forward approved PR
    end
    P->>V: Issue Purchase Order
    V-->>P: Order confirmation
    V->>F: Submit invoice
    F->>F: 3-way match verification
    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION
    alt 3-way match passes
        F-->>V: Payment processed (NET30)
    else 3-way match fails (invoice / PO / goods receipt discrepancy)
        Note over F: SOX Control: Invoice hold – discrepancy detected
        F->>F: Place invoice on hold
        F-->>P: Discrepancy notice (mismatch details)
        F-->>V: Discrepancy notice (mismatch details)
        V->>P: Submit corrected invoice / documentation
        P->>P: Review & verify correction
        P-->>F: Correction confirmed
        F->>F: Re-run 3-way match verification
        F-->>V: Payment processed (NET30)
    end

%% EXPLANATION:
%% Replaced the single payment step after 3-way match with an alt/else block. The happy path (match passes) proceeds directly to payment. The failure path places the invoice on hold, sends discrepancy notices to both Procurement and the Vendor, waits for the Vendor to submit corrections through Procurement, requires Procurement's explicit confirmation, triggers a re-run of the 3-way match, and only then releases payment. A SOX Control annotation marks the hold as an auditable control point. All existing interactions are preserved unchanged.